1. What is DataOps?

DataOps is the tools and processes for monitoring and automating tasks and
software that raise the efficiency of operations in support of all data
products and services. And so much more
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij2JQogBVqaA3S6-gJTepNSYHga=
ahQNq_EGOhAVNGX9XN0DHCp_6Zc0BisGIPrLJiNcR0=3D>
.

*+* *Getting DataOps Right
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij2EG0mUDFGJRH7LWPBATNpaeH-=
azx68nEYTTGBMCZ6Ri8GQmrIG-E6hhG8LUQtxqx8Aw=3D>*

2. The missing piece of the data stack

What we're missing is a metrics layer. Benn Stancil explains
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij2AUm_dx0IMIlASqQ6LDnOmurU=
CFZjzEtm0jiGYjvOMjQTl0OnRUAqpU4DAsjWtHgY4Y=3D>
.

*+* "Is Minerva the Answer?
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij122xLZj75yNm6zKgWTqKh3U-W=
Xe3fyCn2KeFdjWhMHhN0-lKPwCK7RROxJmnzG4NnAM=3D>
"
+ "How Airbnb Achieved Metric Consistency at Scale
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij2F3ceMOmhYsVZKPzX6mogbtoc=
jCHJ6Md19fRW2NSpAKIorNrwpDTwyw_L2FOFyu4htE=3D>"


3. Applying ML in an internal audit (with sparsely labeled data) at Uber

This case study
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij2ALTQedaqa9m2NhOTx8fIE6pK=
ScQh32hpT6I00Ndjdpr0lPg-h6F-9piivslqT8n5kY=3D>
shows how the Uber engineering team used ML to solve one particular
auditing problem at the company. Uber's methodology and architecture could
be useful for a range of other audit-related data problems.

4. Online resource allocation with Ray at Ant Group

Ant Group implemented a flexible, high-performance, stable, and scalable
online resource allocation system based on Ray. The system=E2=80=99s deploy=
ment
scale has reached more than 6000 CPU cores and has a wide range of use
cases. Here's a look at how they did it
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij2Oi7TYHaFCRdv173psDMPdDBu=
8xSmLT_PEaBTaDNo45K93i8buMKQWZ31qjnIRezkq4=3D>
.

*+* Data Science with Big Datasets Using Dask, Ray, and Other Best-of-Breed
Tools
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij1-vHQ3Epseix43BbkgzmDT3my=
W3LenEQyoten66PyPosO4Uhu4HDduyVzE5Isd8mMJ0=3D>,
a live online O'Reilly course, May 27

5. Want to fix AI in the private sector? Fix it in the military first.

"The best place to answer the question of '*How do we build AI in a way
that prevents unethical and unsafe outcomes?'* is in the environment that
has the most to lose from unethical and unsafe AI. That will never be
Google, or Facebook, or Twitter. Recent events have demonstrated this. The
best place to work on ethical AI and safe software is with the people for
whom the stakes are greater than missed revenue targets." In this post
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij2AhZvuhGMEBZqUxaGovzyN6rs=
Bj5BQYYjANNnkNs9NJbneyMj35SN-2K1QxWLF8de0s=3D>,
Marianne Bellotti, author of *Kill It with Fire: Manage Aging Computer
Systems (and Future Proof Modern Ones*)
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij18dORgbT15f9XAnk8YS0L2ZRV=
MbdSruXWgwNWCb8E67F9ITmOU54TADu9LsQbUR-eJE=3D>
explains how the DoD can set the standard.

New release: *Mastering Shiny*
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij2CEajUen6OqnfDoipzHsEzdP1=
2GbKkNe0TPzwuw1jt5pRBQWSckp_4yf6wLxcSpt7VU=3D>

By letting you move beyond static reports, Shiny helps you create fully
interactive web apps for data analyses. You can jump between datasets,
explore different subsets or facets of the data, run models with parameter
values of their choosing, customize visualizations, and much more. Even if
you have no knowledge of HTML, CSS, or JavaScript, this practical guide
will show you how to create rich web apps from R.
Read it on O=E2=80=99Reilly
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij2CEajUen6OqnfDoipzHsEzdP1=
2GbKkNe0TPzwuw1jt5pRBQWSckp_4yf6wLxcSpt7VU=3D>
See it on Amazon
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij2JCrb8jnh8dyohbYEtFihD2BK=
ghG4eK9MC13Ks5OxeCFsSmRKpoJYmU5ec_1umB5lBo=3D>


6. A new AI model for fighting disease faster

One of the most promising uses for AI is predicting effective drug
"cocktails" for complex diseases. Facebook AI and the Helmholtz Zentrum
M=C3=BCnchen have built (and open-sourced) an AI model that predicts the ef=
fects
of drug combinations, dosages, timing, and even other types of intervention=
s
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij2Pvo198XxR7xzb8qaZ3FszhHf=
4gsEg3UY3Kn4l_AxFsV5kuRPTYNPP7FBoJoCyw6PRM=3D>,
such as gene knockout or deletion.

7. Data strategies that can help drive business value at scale

"Conventional modes of data engineering and data architecture have largely
failed to deliver on the promises that were made when the Big Data
revolution happened. Part of the reason is that these centralized
structures simply don=E2=80=99t scale with the number of use cases. We=E2=
=80=99re not bound
by our imagination. We=E2=80=99re not limited by our ability to seek insigh=
t. We=E2=80=99re
limited by our ability to find high-quality data that we can trust,=E2=80=
=9D says
Emily Gorcenski. This post
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij2EKxKhvuV4GNxTE6w7J_YEe77=
c9VhgyI_IS3VBIA6-wli--jpdi2dHJv7lZhrQY_lv4=3D>
describes data strategies that can help drive business value at scale.

8. Ethics? It=E2=80=99s time to talk about power.

In this interview
<https://link.oreilly.com/MTA3LUZNUy0wNzAAAAF89tij2EPkdSUSCQ7JsTpGi13DCv3J1=
UB1iPGNiJKxsaf7jOx6Pb4-h5oO5CVeWg6ggrWHyEY=3D>,
Kate Crawford says AI is neither artificial nor intelligent and we need to
acknowledge both the politics and the physical impact that AI has on the
planet.



